eror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":87,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":96,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Ruddlan was born about 1128, in England, his father, Matthew de Ruddlan, was 43 and his mother, Mrs. Matthew de Ruddlan, was 38. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Beatrice De Ruddlan."},"et":{"about 1128–":"umbes 1128–Surnud","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1087–Male":"1087–Surnud","1092–Female":"1092–Surnud","1128":"1128","1215":"1215","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1224":"1224","1135":"1135","about 1128":"umbes 1128","1087":"1087","1160":"1160","1092":"1092","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1128–":"noin 1128–Kuollut","1128–Male":"1128–Kuollut","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1087–Male":"1087–Kuollut","1092–Female":"1092–Kuollut","1128":"1128","1215":"1215","about 1160":"noin 1160","1224":"